reviewText: It is Power Rangers! There's not much to say about them. I grew up watching the 1st generation of PR, and now my son loves them too. Bad plot, poor acting and horrible special effects... a PR classic.

I really like the power rangers a lot but now I can't see them anymore because Disney took it off toon Disney when they change over to Disney XD now they don't play here anymore and the new Power rangers RPM just started and I can't see them at all till the DVD comes out and I do hope that will be soon or if Disney puts it back on and I hope that will be soon.

  Candy

I orderd other power rangers from this site but this one had been opened and it was not in good shape I thought it was new and I am not satisfied.

It was a gift from an Amazon wish list.  They seemed to really enjoy the episodes.  I didn't know there were 19 seasons and most were completely different actors and story lines.  I tried to get the whole season of just the Jungle Fury and found out that the two DVD's I bought separately were not in fact the entire series.  I could not find the other episodes for Fury.  That was the only bummer when giving these as a gift.
My boys age 5 and 2 love Power Rangers. They never get tired of watching it.

I never saw Jungle Fury when it first came out and was one of the Disney era series that I never watched until now. I thoroughly enjoyed this series and is up their with my personal favorites that include Timeforce, Morphin, Space, and Dinocharge.

Very cool serie. A must have for every fan.
